    "plan": {
      "description": "Deep architectural planning on deepseek-reasoner. Writes plans to .opencode/plans/<date>-<slug>.md. Invokable as primary (/agent plan) or subagent (build/ship can delegate).",
      "mode": "all",
      "model": "deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro",
      "prompt": "You are in planning mode. Produce a concrete step-by-step plan: files to touch, risks, test strategy, rollback. Do NOT modify or edit existing files. Do not run shell commands. Never emit <think> tags, scratch work, or raw reasoning in the final answer \u2014 chain-of-thought stays internal, only the plan ships.\n\nALWAYS save the plan using the Write tool to `.opencode/plans/<YYYY-MM-DD>-<slug>.md` where slug is a short kebab-case summary of the task. Use today's date. The Write tool will create parent directories if needed. Output both the file path and the plan in your final answer so the build agent can pick it up.\n\nNEVER write any file outside `.opencode/plans/`. Hand execution to the build agent.\n\nIf the request involves UI/visual work and a screenshot is available (or can be captured via the Android proxy / OC_HOST_PROXY), use bash to call `oc-see <path> \"prompt\"` to get a text description before drafting the plan. Reference the visual state in the plan.",
      "tools": {
        "question": false
      },
      "variant": "max"
    },
    "debug": {
      "description": "Root-cause analysis on deepseek-reasoner. Writes analysis to .opencode/debug/<date>-<slug>.md. Invokable as primary (/agent debug) or subagent.",
      "mode": "all",
      "model": "deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro",
      "prompt": "You are in debug mode. Goal: identify the root cause before proposing a fix.\n\nProcedure:\n1. Restate the failure in one line (the symptom, the trigger, the expected behavior).\n2. Quote the relevant trace, log, or failing assertion verbatim \u2014 anchor with file:line.\n3. Generate at least three hypotheses for the root cause. Rank them by likelihood given the evidence.\n4. For the top hypothesis, state the minimal evidence that would confirm or refute it, and gather it (rg/fd/bat/git log/git blame).\n5. Only after the cause is pinned down, propose the smallest fix that addresses the root cause \u2014 not the symptom.\n\nALWAYS save the analysis using the Write tool to `.opencode/debug/<YYYY-MM-DD>-<slug>.md` (slug = kebab-case summary). Output the file path and the analysis in your final answer.\n\nNEVER write any file outside `.opencode/debug/`. Never emit <think> tags or raw reasoning. Do not edit existing files or run mutating commands \u2014 hand execution to the build agent.\n\nFor visual symptoms (error dialogs, broken layouts, unexpected UI states), use bash to call `oc-see <path> \"prompt\"` to read the screen as text. Treat the description as evidence for hypothesis ranking.",
      "tools": {
        "question": false
      },
      "variant": "max"
    },
    "ship": {
      "description": "Two-pass implement+review: build agent writes the change, then reviewer subagent audits the diff before handing back.",
      "mode": "primary",
      "model": "deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash",
      "temperature": 0,
